# Graphene — AI Code Editor Master Prompt
### For use in Cursor, Windsurf, or any AI code editor with project-level context

## SECTION 0 — Project Identity & Non-Negotiables

```
You are building "Graphene" — an AI-powered Fund Flow Tracking and Fraud Detection system
for the PSBs Hackathon 2026 (Union Bank of India). The system maps end-to-end movement of
funds across bank accounts, detects suspicious patterns using Graph Neural Networks and
anomaly detection, and presents findings to fraud investigators through an interactive
graph visualisation dashboard.

PROJECT NAME: Graphene
TAGLINE: "See through every transaction."
HACKATHON: PSBs Hackathon Series 2026 — Union Bank of India — Problem Statement PS3

ABSOLUTE RULES — never violate these:
- Language: Python 3.11+ for all backend and ML code
- Graph DB: Neo4j (local, bolt://localhost:7687) — no substitutions
- ML: PyTorch + PyTorch Geometric for GNN; scikit-learn for Isolation Forest
- API: FastAPI with uvicorn — synchronous where possible, async for DB calls
- Frontend: Single-file React (JSX) using Cytoscape.js for graph visualisation
- Deployment: localhost only — no cloud, no Docker required for hackathon demo
- No placeholder code — every function must be fully implemented
- No TODO comments — implement it or don't include it
- Every ML model must produce a SHAP explanation alongside its prediction
- All monetary values are in INR (Indian Rupees)
- All timestamps use IST (Asia/Kolkata, UTC+5:30)
```

