## SECTION 5 — API Layer

### 5a. Prompt: FastAPI Main App

```
FILE: api/main.py

Create the Graphene FastAPI application.

SETUP:
- App title: "Graphene API", version: "1.0.0"
- CORS: allow all origins (localhost demo — no restrictions needed)
- Startup event: verify Neo4j connection, load ML models into memory
- Shutdown event: close Neo4j driver cleanly
- Mount static files at /static → frontend/ directory
- Root route GET / → serve frontend/index.html

MIDDLEWARE:
- Request logging: log method, path, status, duration for every request
- Error handler: catch all unhandled exceptions → return JSON {error, detail, timestamp}

INCLUDE ROUTERS:
- api/routes/health.py    → prefix="/api"
- api/routes/alerts.py    → prefix="/api"
- api/routes/graph.py     → prefix="/api"
- api/routes/reports.py   → prefix="/api"

STARTUP SEQUENCE (lifespan):
1. Connect to Neo4j — fail fast if unavailable
2. Load GNN model from ml/models/gnn_best.pt
3. Load AnomalyDetector from ml/models/anomaly_detector.pkl
4. Run all 5 pattern queries on startup, cache results in memory
5. Compute risk scores for all accounts, cache in memory
6. Log: "Graphene API ready — X accounts loaded, Y alerts generated"
```

### 5b. Prompt: API Routes

```
FILE: api/routes/alerts.py

ENDPOINTS:

GET /api/alerts
  Query params: tier (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH/CRITICAL), limit (default 50), offset (0)
  Returns: paginated list of alerts sorted by risk_score desc
  Response: {total, alerts: [...], page_info: {...}}

GET /api/alerts/{alert_id}
  Returns: full alert with SHAP explanation, pattern details, account metadata
  404 if not found

PATCH /api/alerts/{alert_id}
  Body: {status: "INVESTIGATING" | "DISMISSED" | "ESCALATED", analyst_note: str}
  Updates alert status in Neo4j (write back)
  Returns: updated alert

GET /api/alerts/stats
  Returns: {total_alerts, by_tier: {LOW, MEDIUM, HIGH, CRITICAL},
            top_patterns: [{pattern, count}], total_amount_at_risk: float}

---
FILE: api/routes/graph.py

ENDPOINTS:

GET /api/graph/{account_id}
  Query params: depth (1-4, default 2)
  Returns: Cytoscape.js-ready graph JSON:
  {
    nodes: [{data: {id, label, risk_score, risk_tier, account_type,
                    total_sent, total_received, is_flagged}}],
    edges: [{data: {id, source, target, amount, txn_type, timestamp,
                    is_fraud, fraud_type}}]
  }

POST /api/graph/trace
  Body: {source_account: str, dest_account: str}
  Returns: shortest path between accounts as Cytoscape graph JSON
  Includes: path length, total amount, intermediate accounts

GET /api/graph/patterns
  Returns: all detected pattern instances grouped by type
  Each instance includes: involved_accounts, transaction_ids, total_amount

---
FILE: api/routes/reports.py

ENDPOINTS:

POST /api/reports/generate
  Body: {alert_id: str, analyst_name: str, analyst_id: str}
  Generates a PDF Suspicious Transaction Report (STR) formatted for FIU-IND
  Returns: {report_id, download_url, generated_at}

GET /api/reports/{report_id}/download
  Streams the PDF file as application/pdf response

The STR PDF must contain:
  - Graphene header with logo (text-based, no image needed)
  - Reporting entity: Union Bank of India (for demo)
  - Subject account details (name, account number, branch)
  - Risk score and tier with visual indicator
  - All triggered AML patterns with evidence
  - Full SHAP explanation in plain English
  - Transaction table: top 20 suspicious transactions
  - Graph summary: accounts involved, total amount
  - Analyst signature block
  - FIU report number (generated UUID), date, time (IST)

Use reportlab or weasyprint for PDF generation.
```

