FILE: ml/train.py

Implement a CLI-runnable training script:

python ml/train.py --epochs 100          # full training
python ml/train.py --epochs 30 --fast    # demo mode (use cached features if available)

Steps:
1. Load features from Neo4j (or cache)
2. Train GNN model → save to ml/models/gnn_best.pt
3. Train AnomalyDetector → save to ml/models/anomaly_detector.pkl
4. Run all pattern queries → save results to ml/models/pattern_cache.json
5. Compute risk scores for all accounts → save to ml/models/risk_scores.json
6. Print final summary:
   "Training complete.
    GNN AUC-ROC: 0.XXX | Precision: 0.XX | Recall: 0.XX
    Anomaly Detector: X accounts flagged
    Patterns detected: X circular, X layering, X structuring, X dormant, X mismatch
    Total CRITICAL alerts: X | HIGH: X | MEDIUM: X"
