## SECTION 9 — Code Quality Rules

```
Enforce these rules on ALL generated code:

STYLE:
- Type hints on every function signature (Python)
- Docstrings on every class and public method (Google style)
- Max line length: 88 characters (black formatter compatible)
- No magic numbers — all constants in a CONFIG dict at top of file

ERROR HANDLING:
- Never use bare except: — always except SpecificException as e:
- Log all exceptions with: logger.exception("Context message")
- API endpoints return structured errors: {error: str, detail: str, code: int}

LOGGING:
- Use Python's logging module — not print() in production code
- Format: "[GRAPHENE] %(levelname)s %(name)s — %(message)s"
- Level: INFO for normal operations, DEBUG for query results, ERROR for failures

TESTING:
- Every function in data/ and ml/ must have a corresponding test in tests/
- Use pytest — test file mirrors source file name: test_gnn_model.py
- At minimum: one happy path test, one edge case, one error case

PERFORMANCE:
- All Neo4j queries: add LIMIT clause (max 1000 rows unless explicitly paginated)
- Feature computation: cache to disk, reload if <1 hour old
- Model inference: batch all accounts, never call model one account at a time
- API response time target: <500ms for graph queries, <200ms for alert list
```

