## QUICK REFERENCE — Build Order for Hackathon

```
Build in this exact order to always have a runnable demo:

Day 1 — Core data pipeline:
  ✅ data/generate_transactions.py   (synthetic data with fraud patterns)
  ✅ data/fraud_patterns.py           (plant AML patterns)
  ✅ data/seed_neo4j.py               (load into Neo4j)
  ✅ graph/neo4j_client.py            (DB connection)
  ✅ graph/pattern_queries.py         (Cypher AML detection)
  → CHECKPOINT: You can query Neo4j and see fraud patterns in Cypher shell

Day 2 — ML models:
  ✅ ml/feature_engineering.py        (extract features)
  ✅ ml/anomaly_detector.py           (Isolation Forest)
  ✅ ml/gnn_model.py                  (GraphSAGE)
  ✅ ml/shap_explainer.py             (explanations)
  ✅ ml/risk_scorer.py                (ensemble 0-100 score)
  ✅ ml/train.py                      (full pipeline)
  → CHECKPOINT: python ml/train.py prints AUC scores and alert counts

Day 3 — API + Dashboard:
  ✅ api/main.py + routes/            (FastAPI endpoints)
  ✅ frontend/index.html              (full Graphene dashboard)
  ✅ run_demo.sh                      (one-command launcher)
  → CHECKPOINT: Full demo running at http://localhost:8000

Day 4 — Polish:
  ✅ README.md                        (judges may read this)
  ✅ Dry-run the demo script 3 times
  ✅ Test with Neo4j stopped → graceful error message, not crash
  ✅ Verify PDF report generates correctly
  ✅ Rehearse 8-minute demo script
```

